wally - animated wallpaper for X11
===================================
wally is a minimal animated wallpaper utility that plays GIFs and videos
on your X11 root window. It does one thing and does it well.

Requirements
------------
- X11
- giflib
- ffmpeg (libavformat, libavcodec, libavutil, libswscale)

Installation
------------
Enter the following command to build and install wally
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install

Running wally
-------------
Simply invoke the 'wally' command with a file:

    wally animation.gif

This will play the animation on your root window in a loop.

Options
-------
    -c            center on screen
    -f            fill screen (may crop)
    -s            scale to fit screen
    -o            set once and exit (for startup scripts)

Supported formats: gif, mp4, webm, mkv

Examples
--------
Play a GIF scaled to fit:

    wally -s ~/wallpapers/cat.gif

Fill screen with a video:

    wally -f ~/videos/rain.mp4

Set wallpaper on login (add to .xinitrc):

    wally -o -f ~/wallpapers/space.gif &

Center a small animation:

    wally -c animation.gif
